                    <name type="place">New York,</name> 
                    <date when="1891-11-02"><handShift rend="manuscript"/>Nov 2
                            <handShift rend="printed"/> 
                            18
                            <handShift rend="manuscript"/>
                            91
                        </date>
                    
                </dateline>
                <salute>Walt Whitman Esq.</salute>
               <salute>Camden, N.J.</salute>
                <salute>Dear Sir,<ptr target="loc.07425_n2"/></salute>
            </opener>
            <p>
                One who is glad to see the world, at last, willing to
                crown the <hi rend="underline">only original</hi>
                American Poet with the laurels of undying fame:
                sends you greeting: the enclosed <unclear reason="illegible" resp="#cn" cert="low">S</unclear>on
                <gap reason= "cut away" quantity="3" unit="words"/>  
                have already "said  
                <gap reason= "cut away" quantity="2" unit="words"/>
                give lectures or a little charity,
                <gap reason= "cut away" quantity="4" unit="words"/>
                <gap reason= "cut away" quantity="2" unit="chars"/>ve
                out of myself."
                <gap reason= "cut away" quantity="3" unit="words"/>
                in my power to make
                <gap reason= "cut away" quantity="3" unit="words"/>
                comfort for the noble heart
                <gap reason= "cut away" quantity="3" unit="words"/>
                <gap reason= "cut away" quantity="4" unit="chars"/>lined in
                <gap reason= "cut away" quantity="3" unit="words"/>
                and Democracy and the
                <gap reason= "cut away" quantity="3" unit="words"/>
                <gap reason= "cut away" quantity="1" unit="chars"/>eligion."
            </p>
            <closer> 
                <salute><gap reason= "cut away" quantity="3" unit="chars"/>ever</salute>
                <signed><hi rend="underline">Henry Hopkins</hi></signed>
            </closer>
